# Purpose

Market Breadth evaluates the participation quality of the overall market.

Rather than measuring index movement alone, Market Breadth determines whether market gains or losses are broadly supported across securities, sectors, and industries.

A healthy market requires broad participation.

Weak breadth indicates that only a few large-cap stocks are driving the index.

Market Breadth is a leading indicator for trend sustainability.

